stdyInfo.abstract:
This is a dataset of roll-call votes in the UN General Assembly 1946-2012. It also contains Affinity of Nations scores and ideal point estimates derived from these votes. The Bailey, Strezhnev, and Voeten paper cited below explains why ideal point estimates rather than Affinity scores should be used.
Please consult the codebooks for more detailed information. Please also consult the following paper for a discussion of common errors in using the data:
Voeten, Erik, Data and Analyses of Voting in the UN General Assembly (July 17, 2012). Available at SSRN: http://ssrn.com/abstract=2111149
Bailey, Michael and Strezhnev, Anton and Voeten, Erik, Estimating Dynamic State Preferences from United Nations Voting Data (September 25, 2013). Available at SSRN: http://ssrn.com/abstract=2330913 or http://dx.doi.org/10.2139/ssrn.2330913
